# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Bundled OCR binaries (~286 MB).
# Rebuilt locally by `python scripts/fetch_vendor_tesseract.py`. Not committed
# because (a) they're upstream binaries we don't want to vendor into git LFS
# and (b) any release machine that needs Tesseract for OCR re-runs the fetch
# script as part of the build prerequisites check.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
vendor/cache/
vendor/tesseract/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Israeli CVFR/LSA chart PDFs at the repo root (e.g. CVFR-NORTH-OCT-2025-*.pdf).
# Redistribution is prohibited by the source's (CAAI) terms of use, so the raw
# charts are NEVER committed — the app downloads them at runtime from the URLs
# in chart_sources.json. Scoped to the repo root (`/`) so test-fixture and
# documentation PDFs living in subdirectories are unaffected.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
/*.pdf

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Per-project runtime cache (~65 MB).
# Populated the first time the app launches against the CVFR PDFs (OCR'd
# waypoints, normalised map PNGs, altitude arrow extractions, the user's
# personal calibration). Both reproducible from the chart PDFs and tied
# to a specific machine's calibration — no value in committing.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.cvfr_routemaster/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Per-user app preferences (INI format, project-root-local).
# Holds window layout, font sizes, satellite-download notice flag,
# QSettings-style key/value preferences — see settings_store.SETTINGS_INI_FILENAME.
# Lives next to the EXE in release builds (which is .gitignored as release/)
# and next to the repo root in dev mode. Never committed because it's
# per-machine and per-developer; v3.3+ replaced the per-platform native
# QSettings backend (Windows registry / Linux ~/.config / macOS plist) with
# this INI file so wipe-the-folder equals wipe-the-state.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
settings.ini

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PyInstaller / release build outputs.
# All three are derived artifacts; the source-of-truth is the spec files
# (cvfr-routemaster.spec, cvfr-routemaster-linux.spec) plus the scripts in
# scripts/build_release*.py. `cvfr-routemaster-linux.tar.gz` is the bundled
# Linux release archive emitted by the Linux build script (~374 MB) and is
# regenerated end-to-end on every build.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
build/
dist/
release/
release-linux/
cvfr-routemaster-linux.tar.gz
release-build.log

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Runtime logs the app dumps next to the executable (Qt logging + stderr/
# stdout captures used while debugging the WSL launch issue). Per-session,
# never part of a release.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.cvfr.err
.cvfr.log
.cvfr.out

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Python bytecode / pytest scratch.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
.coverage.*
htmlcov/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# WSL-side scratch directory used while diagnosing the Linux build (mtime
# investigations, py-spy dumps, etc.). Not part of the source tree.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.wsl-scratch/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local scratch / experimentation folder. Houses one-off benchmark scripts,
# probe utilities and other throwaway code that helped diagnose specific
# bugs but isn't part of the product. Anything graduated into the real tree
# (cvfr_routemaster/, scripts/, tests/) ceases to be scratch.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
scratch/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# User flight-plan saves and CSV waypoint exports written via the in-app
# "Save flight plan" / "Export waypoints to CSV" dialogs. The default save
# location is the repo root when launching from `py -m cvfr_routemaster`,
# so these would otherwise pollute the working tree.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.cvfr
waypoints.csv

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Editor / IDE local state.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
.cursor/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OS noise.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store
